President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Scott Gottlieb of Connecticut as Commissioner of Food and Drugs at the Department of Health and Human Services. Dr. Gottlieb is a physician, a resident fellow at the American Enterprise Institute, and a venture partner at New Enterprise Associates. He has a Bachelor of Arts in Economics from Wesleyan University and a Doctor of Medicine from the Mount Sinai School of Medicine. Dr. Gottlieb previously served as the Deputy Commissioner for Medical and Scientific Affairs at the U.S. Food and Drug Administration. He has received awards such as the Visionary in Medicine Award from the Sarcoma Foundation of America and the Food and Drug Administration's Special Recognition Award.